  "blurb": "A rambling 11-bedroom villa set into the Chaweng Noi hills, arranged across stepped levels that follow the slope and open to a wide panorama of Koh Samui's eastern coast. Infinity pools, glass-walled living pavilions and en-suite bedrooms — several with their own sea-facing terraces — make it as convincing a private retreat as it is a high-capacity rental.",
  "detail": "High on the wooded slopes of Chaweng Noi, this expansive residence unfolds across a series of levels tucked into the hillside, each connected by steps and framing the same generous outlook over the sea and the coastline below. With eleven bedrooms and around 651 m² of interior space set on a 2,604 m² freehold plot, it is built for gatherings — large families, groups of friends, or an owner who wants a turnkey income property in one of the island's most sought-after addresses.\n\nThe main living pavilion is wrapped in floor-to-ceiling glass, so the sea view carries through the open-plan lounge and dining area from morning to dusk. Sliding walls fold back to a terrace where an infinity pool meets the horizon, with sun-loungers and shaded lounging spots arranged along the edge. A second pool and further terraces step down the hill, giving the property several distinct places to swim, dine and relax.\n\nEach of the eleven bedrooms has its own en-suite bathroom, and many open onto private balconies that look out across the treetops to the water. Finished in a crisp palette of white walls and dark stone floors, the rooms feel calm and uncluttered, with the greenery of the surrounding gardens pressing close to the glass.\n\nCompleted in 2015 and held on a Chanote freehold title, the villa sits within a short drive of Chaweng's beaches, restaurants and nightlife while remaining screened by dense tropical planting. With its established layout and proven letting appeal, it suits a buyer looking for a substantial hillside home or a ready-run holiday rental with real scale.",
